    "Infractionist Personae - Attitude": {
      "name": "Personajes Infraccionistas - Actitud",
      "description": "<p>Actitud</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "Demasiado confiado y fácilmente provocado a la violencia.",
        "2-2": "Alerta, taciturno, sin paciencia para los que pierden el tiempo o los aficionados.",
        "3-3": "Desconfía absolutamente de la autoridad imperial.",
        "4-4": "No busca problemas, desea que le dejen en paz.",
        "5-5": "De mal genio y despectivo, pero fácilmente intimidado por gente más fuerte o más aterradora.",
        "6-6": "Catastrofista, que detesta a los Tech-Sacerdotes y a los impíos.",
        "7-7": "Trabajador de turno largo, siempre cansado e impaciente por conseguir el descanso que tanto necesita.",
        "8-8": "Obsequioso y adulador, dice lo que cree que la gente quiere escuchar.",
        "9-9": "Le resulta incómodo hablar al descubierto, le gusta tener una pared a su espalda.",
        "10-10": "Exige un concurso de fuerza; el resultado determina si será servicial o burlón."
      }
    },
    "Hive Spire Whispers": {
      "name": "Hive Spire Whispers",
      "description": "<p><strong>Hive Spires:</strong> The most affluent and influential members of hive society dwell among the spires, mingling at the very uppermost levels of these towering metropolises. Seldom deigning to leave these peaks, the nobility dictates the actions and lives of those who live in the lower levels. All the while, they remain isolated in luxury, away from those they designate as their social inferiors. Their primary concern is a mix of their own desires — and what the Imperium requires, the Hive supplies them with. Petty betrayals, family squabbles, and superfluous drama are the crux of many rumours.</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "<p><b>Renegade Activity:</b> “Oh yes, the captain of my  cousin’s Enforcers. Took a crack squad downhive  months ago and hasn’t been seen since, but we  know they’re still active. A delicious scandal!”</p>",
        "2-2": "<p><b>Cult Activity:</b> “How dare he choose friends over  family! I can see it in his eyes, those parties must  be exquisite. Why would the Duchess invite him  over me? How unfair!”</p>",
        "3-3": "<p><b>Xenos Tech:</b> “Our Baron likes to show off his  little curios to whoever he invites round for deals  or dinners. Turns all his gatherings into great  successes, they say, but never mentions where he  sources these strange objects.”</p>",
        "4-4": "<p><b>Archaeotech:</b> “I’ve heard the Tech-Priests are  excited, insofar as that lot can be. I gather they  found something interesting amongst the spire’s  power cells, so now we must endure lengthy  delays to their repair.”</p>",
        "5-5": "<p><b>Heretical Healer:</b> “I don’t envy that healer. Yes,  those nobles are now healthier than before their  ailments and he enjoys their personal hospitality.  But every young heir now has decades to wait!”</p>",
        "6-6": "<p><b>Hive Alliances:</b> “I should have those diplomats  flogged! Send another delegation. If we cannot  strike a trade agreement in the sanctum  administratus, we must make perparations to  strike it on the battlefield!”</p>",
        "7-7": "<p><b>Hive Disasters:</b> “I’ve heard it said we lost nine  million workers when that spire collapsed.  The Administratum expects a 15% drop in  productivity. Tell the survivors they are allowed  no more than 10%.”</p>",
        "8-8": "<p><b>Nouveau Riche:</b> “I say, don’t mention that  upstart’s name here! Wherever he found his  fortune, he certainly did not find manners  alongside it! A contemptible braggart. Mother is  just beside herself.”</p>",
        "9-9": "<p><b>Valued Vintage:</b> “This year’s vintage is  magnificent! Well worth the… unusual weather. I  fear with such fervent demand across the system,  we will soon have no reserves to speak of!”</p>",
        "10-10": "<p><b>The Tithe:</b> “Meeting the Tithe is good and  right, praise the God-Emperor and so forth, but  continued success only invites higher Tithes. We  should take steps to ensure our rivals pay any  increase instead of us.”</p>"
      }
    },
    "Noble Titles - Domain": {
      "name": "Noble Titles - Domain",
      "description": "<p>Domain</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "of the Edifice of Krint",
        "2-2": "of the Far March",
        "3-3": "of Hive Level Gamma",
        "4-4": "of House Tavol",
        "5-5": "of the Near Wastes",
        "6-6": "of the Outer Query",
        "7-7": "of Rolokar’s Last Regiment",
        "8-8": "of Sector XR-52",
        "9-9": "of Sub Sector Alpha",
        "10-10": "of the Thirsting Gulf"
      }
    },
    "Adeptus Ministorum Personae - Mannerism": {
      "name": "Adeptus Ministorum Personae - Mannerism",
      "description": "<p>Mannerism</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "They sit perfectly still, peering over their arched fingers.",
        "2-2": "Always quoting benedictions to back up their words.",
        "3-3": "Communicates with sign language or written notes due to a vow of silence.",
        "4-4": "Constantly fiddling with a cilice or other tool of self-mortification.",
        "5-5": "Sips from a hip flask of amasec when they think nobody is watching.",
        "6-6": "Never makes eye contact, as if watching unseen angels near the characters.",
        "7-7": "Smoke issues from their eyes (or sockets) in the presence of religious iconography.",
        "8-8": "Whistles or hums the cadence of common hymns when distracted.",
        "9-9": "Writes down their impressively impure thoughts in a small pocketbook.",
        "10-10": "Twitches at any sudden sound, and constantly implores characters to lower their loud voices."
      }
    },
    "Astra Militarum Personae - Mannerism": {
      "name": "Astra Militarum Personae - Mannerism",
      "description": "<p>Mannerism</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "Obsessively polishes their sidearm.",
        "2-2": "Constantly mopping sweat from their brow.",
        "3-3": "Cleans their nails with a vicious knife while talking.",
        "4-4": "Ends each sentence with a crisp <i>“Sah!”</i>, as if speaking to their superior.",
        "5-5": "Constantly adjusting their hat, as if it is slightly too small.",
        "6-6": "Tilts their head to one side while listening, as if appraising.",
        "7-7": "Looks startled, afraid they’ve been caught doing something unregulated.",
        "8-8": "Constantly flicks the safety clip of their sidearm holster open and closed.",
        "9-9": "Always revising or adding notes to their Guardsman’s Uplifting Primer.",
        "10-10": "Instinctively touches an Aquila on their clothing when they hear “God-Emperor”."
      }
    },
    "Imperial Navy Personae - Distinguishing Feature": {
      "name": "Imperial Navy Personae - Distinguishing Feature",
      "description": "<p>Distinguishing Feature</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "Wears a monocle with a targeting reticle.",
        "2-2": "Low-grav life has made them unusually lithe.",
        "3-3": "Wrapped head to toe in prayer strips and lucky charms.",
        "4-4": "Knuckle tattoos spelling “KILL” on one hand, and “XENO” on the other.",
        "5-5": "Uses a wheelchair of red brass, covered in control panels and data readouts.",
        "6-6": "Looks like they haven’t slept in a month, although their uniform is pristine.",
        "7-7": "An obvious augmetic leg causes every other footstep to clang loudly.",
        "8-8": "Has sewn the dogtags of lost friends into their jacket. It is mostly metal.",
        "9-9": "Their lungs have been replaced with augmetics resembling gas tanks.",
        "10-10": "Retains a servitor to display medals, as they have no more room on their uniform."
      }
    },
    "Imperium Technobabble - First Descriptor": {
