    "Administratum Personae - Attitude": {
      "name": "Administratum Personae - Attitude",
      "description": "<p>Attitude</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "Disdainful and abrasive.",
        "2-2": "Excited to explain administrative minutiae.",
        "3-3": "Paranoid and evasive, convinced enemies are hiding around them.",
        "4-4": "Lazy, will always try to direct claimants to another department.",
        "5-5": "Well-meaning but condescending to anyone of lower rank.",
        "6-6": "Literal-minded, easily confused by jokes or figures of speech.",
        "7-7": "Unusually jovial, happy to be serving the Administratum.",
        "8-8": "They never deviate from protocol, and act apologetically so.",
        "9-9": "Fascinated by non-Administratum personnel.",
        "10-10": "Rather more interested in garnering gossip than focussing on their work."
      }
    },
    "Upper Hive Encounters": {
      "name": "Upper Hive Encounters",
      "description": "",
      "results": {
        "1-7": "The harsh sound of industrial grinding assails your ears as your path takes you alongside the titanic bulk of an @UUID[JournalEntry.arjSGA9gcUykxq0z.JournalEntryPage.XWjIkLBokiwV20Dr#augmetics-manufactorum-phi-99]{Augmetics Manufactorum}. A procession of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#adeptus-mechanicus]{Adeptus Mechanicus} adepts and their servitor guards blocks your path as they carry the fruits of their pious labours — a collection of augmetic limbs arrayed neatly on a palanquin — to another facility.",
        "8-14": "You traverse a maze of habways choked with steam venting from nearby manufactorums, emerging into a small courtyard beneath a towering structural buttress. A winding queue fills the courtyard, waiting for aid from the @UUID[Compendium.impmal-core.items.Item.mEuexXWYb26AVetJ]{Officio Medicae} sanctum built into the buttress itself. Both the @UUID[JournalEntry.WE1MLa1KVRHMD8wJ.JournalEntryPage.t5pIASspATqYLZmG]{Administratum} scriveners keeping records and the ordinates giving medicae aid are clearly overworked, leaving critical information and supplies unattended.",
        "15-21": "Your group passes beneath a tangle of intersecting causeways between thrumming manufactorums, coming upon a plaza interspersed with tall statues and shrines to Macharian Saints. Adepts of Imperial factions mingle, purchasing various religious icons and making pious observances, as a scarred Adeptus Ministorum Preacher screams a sermon to be heard above the industrial noise and the clamour of the crowd.",
        "22-28": "Your travels through habway backstreets entangled with colossal pipes are slowed by a well-armed, cautiously proceeding caravan of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#mercator-lenimen]{Mercator Lenimen} guilders. The guilders demand that everyone keep their distance from their cargo, wary of ambush as they deliver chemicals to an Adeptus Mechanicus Unguentarium.",
        "29-35": "As you pass between the colossal feet of a statue of a saint towering at least a mile high, you hear an argument; a Highborn scion is demanding a tithe of meat from a @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#mercator-carnem]{Mercator Carnem} caravan apparently passing through the noble's territory. If anyone in the argument notices the characters, they will call them over and ask them to settle the debate, potentially representing one side in a duel.",
        "36-42": "Your group exits a miles-long fume-choked passageway into a sanctioned gathering place, a plaza in the loose shape of a gargantuan Aquila emblazoned on the plasteel floor. Though several reasonably well-made market stalls frame the plaza, most milling adepts have their eyes on a raised platform bearing the crest of the @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#mercator-dilaquo]{Mercator Dilaquo}, bidding on containers of water purified to varying degrees.",
        "43-49": "As you navigate a jugle of gantries hanging a mile above the cathedrums on the ground level far below, you pass by a raised plaza outside of a Plasteel Manufactorum. You hear the sharp crack of a @UUID[Compendium.impmal-starter-set.items.Item.jNxvsLBybPPenmmn]{Laspistol} as a pragmatic Departmento Munitorum inspector conducts an unorthodox test of the manufactorum's output.",
        "50-56": "The screeching of maglev trains assail your ears as you pass through an industrial district of the Upper Hive. Your path is blocked by a caravan of @UUID[Compendium.impmal-core.items.Item.0DNYdNKKglMlFOko]{Imperial Fleet} stevadores hauling gargantuan carts laden with goods, brought to a standstill by an Administratum inspection.",
        "57-63": "You find yourselves lost whilst navigating the titanic labyrinth of a habsprawl that spans multiple levels of the @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.9IPqIrShmqynKuZc]{Upper Hive}. Though the majority of the Upper Hive is relatively crime-free, this won’t protect the characters from the ire of the @UUID[Compendium.impmal-starter-set.actors.Actor.O49jTi2TzoFQH5GT]{Macharian Vigilites}. A large squad of @UUID[Compendium.impmal-starter-set.actors.Actor.O49jTi2TzoFQH5GT]{Macharian Vigilites} accosts them, believing they travelled to the Upper Hive illegally, and attempt to escort them to Fortress Precinct Majoris for ‘processing’.",
        "64-70": "Your path takes you through the guts of an enormous thrumming machine, easily taller than a cathedrum, that serves a seemingly indiscernible purpose. Two Tech-Priests examine it, employing arcane devices that by happenstance cause disruption to any technology of your own. Anything you carry that's more complicated than a @UUID[Compendium.impmal-core.items.Item.h1g1g9Rrjt7CnYeW]{Dataslate} is rendered inoperable for one day unless you succeed on a Hard (−20) Tech Test.",
        "71-77": "Your travels take you through a district dominated by a colossal cathedrum whose spires pierce this level of the hive. As you pass beneath its ceiling-scraping arches and incense-choked open cloisters, you cross paths with a group of nervous priests gawking at a squad of @UUID[Compendium.impmal-core.actors.Actor.fR4lfJVppXfiiYea]{Battle Sisters} of the @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#the-order-of-searing-purity]{Order of Searing Purity}. The well-armed @UUID[Compendium.impmal-core.actors.Actor.fR4lfJVppXfiiYea]{Adepta Sororitas} petition any who pass by them to join their righteous witch hunt in the @UUID[RollTable.3naaAiIZQcgzNpZL]{Bowels}.",
        "78-84": "Your group ascend seemingly endless ancient rockrete stairs through a supporting buttress on your way to your destination, but are stopped at a plaza where multiple spiraling staircases meet. The @UUID[JournalEntry.WE1MLa1KVRHMD8wJ.JournalEntryPage.t5pIASspATqYLZmG]{Administratum} are holding a census at this intersection, gathering data on the thousands of varied people passing through at a glacial pace, while @UUID[Compendium.impmal-starter-set.actors.Actor.O49jTi2TzoFQH5GT]{Macharian Vigilites} intimidate anyone attempting to leave without being accounted for.",
        "85-91": "As you travel down a broad throughfare between two multi-mile long cathedrums, your group is enveloped by a procession of thousands of adepts holding a candlelit vigil, aiming to walk the entire breadth of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.K9f5dlvEMBE2fYeW#life-in-rokarth]{Rokarth} in honourable remembrance of the @UUID[Compendium.impmal-core.journals.JournalEntry.B7MZBBT3bNew9N96.JournalEntryPage.X5EFP7IgIUx6CaBW#the-macharian-conquests]{Macharian Crusade}.",
        "92-98": "The group meanders deep through a mazelike district filled with Administratum Sanctums. A stressed scrivener petitions the group, asking them to investigate a location of your choice in the @UUID[RollTable.3naaAiIZQcgzNpZL]{Bowels} to take a population census and investigate any structural instabilities.",
        "99-100": "Choose one of the player characters. As the group traverse the tangled gantries of a bustling habway, you meet eyes with your doppelganger. Their eyes widen, and they throw a @UUID[Compendium.impmal-starter-set.items.Item.kw9N0gOOA3YVqN4i]{Smoke Grenade} on the ground before sprinting away, firing an @UUID[Compendium.impmal-starter-set.items.Item.AfhkWSUYY9y6byiN]{Autopistol} into the crowd to clear a path. The group will have to deal with the aftermath of this confusion, and the character may have to prove it wasn’t them that caused this commotion."
      }
    },
