    "Planetary Transport Whispers": {
      "name": "Planetary Transport Whispers",
      "description": "<p><strong>Planetary Transports:</strong> Movement between a planet’s various settlements and facilities typically depends upon mass transit systems. These include land trains, airships, and submersibles. These enormous vessels might take mere hours or lengthy days to reach their destinations — passengers have plenty of time to interact with each other; where people from opposite ends of the social strata may be forced to mingle in tight quarters. Whispers may be easily traded via idle tongues and sheer boredom, or in nervous anticipation of their journey’s end.</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "<p><b>Missing Cargo:</b> “Passengers are kicking off about  valuables going missing from the holds. But it’s  all under lock and key. If anyone was actually  stealing, where would they put it all anyway?”</p>",
        "2-2": "<p><b>Cult Activity:</b> “You can hear the chants if  you listen close enough, rattling through the  ventilation systems. No idea what they’re chanting  about, but I can’t get the rhythm out of my head.”</p>",
        "3-3": "<p><b>Maintenance Issues:</b> “We’ve been doing our best  with what we’ve got to keep her running, but some  parts you just can’t fix. Deckhands think the ship’s  going to be decommissioned soon.”</p>",
        "4-4": "<p><b>Labour Migration:</b> “Passenger compartments are  overcrowded with labourers getting reassigned to  new locations in the system. None of them are too  happy about getting shifted about.”</p>",
        "5-5": "<p><b>Regional Megafauna:</b> “Birds as big as buildings,  I tell you! That’s what’s keeping us grounded.  This time every year they mess with our transit  windows. The guard’s not going to waste their  munitions on them.”</p>",
        "6-6": "<p><b>Plague:</b> “Passengers on the bottom decks are  coughing and retching, all short of breath. I can  just smell the sickness in the air, can’t you? If it’s  still here when we get to port, the ship will be  quarantined, I have no doubt.”</p>",
        "7-7": "<p><b>Lost Passengers:</b> “Checked the passenger manifest  at the start of my rotation, and there’s a bunch of  them unaccounted for. No-one knows who they  are either. Better find ‘em quick.”</p>",
        "8-8": "<p><b>Signs of Heresy:</b> “Don’t look like any kind of  regular pilgrims to me, not like I’ve ever seen.  Half of them are totally wrapped up in bandages;  everyone’s saying they’ve got something to hide.”</p>",
        "9-9": "<p><b>Colonisation Edict:</b> “The hold’s jam-packed with  folk that don’t want to be there. Mass conscripted,  all their lives uprooted and forced to colonise a  frontier world. They’ll make trouble for all of us,  sooner or later.”</p>",
        "10-10": "<p><b>Renegade Activity:</b> “Changing course will add  more than a week to the journey; Captain’s taking  us past some anomaly, no matter what. The  Imperial Navy will escort us, I’m sure.”</p>"
      }
    },
    "Adeptus Ministorum Personae - Distinguishing Feature": {
      "name": "Adeptus Ministorum Personae - Distinguishing Feature",
      "description": "<p>Distinguishing Feature</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "Heavy keloid scarring across half their face.",
        "2-2": "An Electroflail replaces their left forearm.",
        "3-3": "The mark of the Aquila branded into their forehead.",
        "4-4": "A prayer scroll nailed into their chest, the wound has not healed.",
        "5-5": "A Servo-Skull follows them, swinging an incense thurible.",
        "6-6": "Crudely sharpened teeth, causing their lips to continuously bleed.",
        "7-7": "A flat and expansive nose, clearly broken many times over.",
        "8-8": "A lit brazier is affixed to their head. They reek of scorched flesh.",
        "9-9": "A flowing robe, displaying animated flames.",
        "10-10": "A shrill and scratchy voice, caused by a malfunctioning vox-amplifier unit."
