    "Fumble": {
      "name": "Fumble",
      "description": "<p>Fumble for Starter set</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-2": "<p>You flail inelegantly, and take a few crucial seconds to reassert a defensible stance. You fall to the bottom of  the Initiative order on the next Round.</p>",
        "3-4": "<p>A poorly controlled swing or shot causes you to lurch and drop your weapon. You drop the weapon you used  to attack. Anyone in Immediate Range can pick it up with an Action.</p>",
        "5-6": "<p>You stumble due to an unwieldy swing or unexpected recoil. You fall <i>Prone</i>.</p>",
        "7-8": "<p>Your ungainly attack manages to briefly blind or deafen you. Perhaps you overloaded a plasma weapon,  causing a searing burst of light, used a Loud weapon too close to your ear, or clumsily struck your own eye  when your attack ricocheted. Your are <i>Blinded</i> or <i>Deafened</i>, whichever is determined more appropriate for your weapon by the GM.</p>",
        "9-10": "<p>In the fumbling confusion of battle, you manage to clumsily strike yourself with a glancing blow. You are  either <i>Stunned</i> or <i>Bleeding</i>, whichever is determined more appropriate for your weapon by the GM.</p>"
      }
    },
    "Archivium Whispers": {
      "name": "Archivium Whispers",
      "description": "<p><strong>Archiviums:</strong> The Macharian Sector’s records are stored in vast and secure facilities, scattered about the whole sector. Here, autoquills and cogitators constantly analyse and duplicate documentation for long-term storage. There is always plenty of foot traffic coming and going from Archiviums, as people request and supply documentation, or meet with Administratum agents for interviews; idle talk keenly following in their wake. Rumours can spread from the loose lipped scribes, overworked Adepts, or the abundance of bored visitants.</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "<p><b>Inquisitorial Investigation</b>: “Archive 312-Kappa  is a mess! Some interlopers left records lying  everywhere or missing entirely! I can’t even file a  complaint about the perpetrators, their security  codes mark them as Inquisitorial agents.”</p>",
        "2-2": "<p><b>Lost Fleet</b>: “Oh, you find these now and then in  the archives. They say more than one fleet was lost  during the Macharian Crusade, their astropaths  suddenly falling silent after a warp transition. File  it with all the other ‘pending reply’ reports...”</p>",
        "3-3": "<p><b>Rogue Trader Activity</b>: “These Trade Dynasties  ignore the economic turmoil left in their wake.  Their negligent record keeping will take years to  fix! Market upheaval! Political instability!”</p>",
        "4-4": "<p><b>Famine</b>: “An almost planet-wide famine. Millions  have surely starved, but we cannot simply reroute  supplies from elsewhere. It may be needed for  battlefronts. Besides, the paperwork is incomplete.”</p>",
        "5-5": "<p><b>Xenos Activity</b>: “Priority reports of xenos raids  must be accompanied by corroborating forms  signed by the Militarum officer authorising the  counter-response. Those worlds must rely on their  faith in the God-Emperor for now.”</p>",
        "6-6": "<p><b>Renegades</b>: “Had the requests been processed  correctly, these sub-sector shortages would have  pointed to the world preparing to rebel. But I  heard some scribe lost them, and lost a world  along with them!”</p>",
        "7-7": "<p><b>Unpaid Tithes</b>: “Ah yes, a filing error led to the  world’s Tithe going uncollected for three centuries.  Several generations of soldiers, in need of a war.  Well, the sector’s generals will be pleased.”</p>",
        "8-8": "<p><b>Unexpected Surplus</b>: “Every ship in the sector is  full, and there’s still a ration surplus. If we don’t  find more space, the rest will rot in silos, and  discontent will spread through the farmers’ ranks  like wildfire!”</p>",
        "9-9": "<p><b>Forgotten System</b>: “There’s no mention of the  system in any official maps. It might be a filing  error. It might have been struck from records on  pain of death. I’m not finding out which!”</p>",
        "10-10": "<p><b>Damaged Records</b>: “Oh, Archive 1313-Sigma.  Tragic loss. Priceless records damaged by vermin.  Decontamination protocols somehow missed the  infestation. If you ask me, it was an inside job.”</p>"
      }
    },
    "Voidship Deck Whispers": {
      "name": "Voidship Deck Whispers",
      "description": "<p><strong>Voidship Decks:</strong> A voidship could include the vessels of the Imperial Navy (merchant and military), those captained by Rogue Traders, or even simpler transports or haulers. Many voidcraft have been in service for millennia, with crews who have served aboard for generations. Even travellers sometimes spend decades on a single transit. Through this time, each vessel develops its own culture and personality, while passengers and crew adapt to the cramped conditions — it’s never long before everyone knows some piece of information about anyone aboard.</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "<p><b>Warp Eruptions:</b> “I hate this system. The warp  spewed its vileness here not long ago. We’re not  making any transitions, but pray twice as hard all  the same, lest that vileness get any ideas.”</p>",
        "2-2": "<p><b>Gang Activity:</b> “Don’t venture into the lowest  service level. Gangs of outcast crew down there,  cannibals and worse. Fix problems from the deck  above or leave it be, for all our sakes.”</p>",
        "3-3": "<p><b>Cult Activity:</b> “Some of the crew have a get-together after every warp transit. Kind of a  tradition. They swap stories and say which prayers  or rites helped get them through.”</p>",
        "4-4": "<p><b>Xenos Activity:</b> “Gun crews say they didn’t look  like Imperial ships. They followed us all through  the system. Never got the order to fire. The captain  knows something we don’t.”</p>",
        "5-5": "<p><b>Spoiled Provisions:</b> “Blasted vermin got into the  food storage, contaminated everything but the gray  rations. Strict rationing until we resupply. Even the  officers are eating it unflavoured.”</p>",
        "6-6": "<p><b>Cargo Activity:</b> “Someone’s been damaging  cargo. Security saw nothing. Stowaways, maybe?  Deckhand with a grudge? Sooner or later, they’ll  damage something the officers care about, then  their heads will roll.”</p>",
        "7-7": "<p><b>Engine Instability:</b> “Cog-heads say the main  engine is angry, stopping and starting, can’t be  placated until we dock. Long trip ahead, and God-Emperor help us if we get attacked without thrust.”</p>",
        "8-8": "<p><b>Pirate Activity:</b> “Pirates have been getting worse  where we’re headed. The moment we leave the Sea  of Souls, keep one hand on your weapon and pray  we don’t get noticed.”</p>",
        "9-9": "<p><b>Strange Stowaways:</b> “The Geller Field sprung a  leak last warp transition, now there’s hundreds  of deck labourers mucking about that no one can  remember. They seem to be doing their jobs… but  I just don’t trust them.”</p>",
        "10-10": "<p><b>Rogue Psyker:</b> “That rating will be promoted  within the week. Years in the background, then  they finally speak up and they could persuade an  Ork to bathe. Command staff ’s darling since the  last warp transition.”</p>"
      }
    },
    "Rogue Trader Dynasty Personae - Attitude": {
      "name": "Rogue Trader Dynasty Personae - Attitude",
      "description": "<p>Attitude</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "Eager for excitement, likely to leap to conclusions or impulsive strategies.",
        "2-2": "Headstrong, always trying to goad people into making bets with them.",
        "3-3": "Almost offensively pompous, arrogant, and flirtatious in equal measure.",
        "4-4": "Dull and unsociable, but very keen and experienced regarding financial matters.",
        "5-5": "Friendly, but not totally sane, occasionally speaks in rhyme or metaphor.",
        "6-6": "Is suspicious of puritanical imperials, knowing much about xenos cultures.",
        "7-7": "Deeply pious, all their conversations come out sounding like a sermon.",
        "8-8": "Always complaining about the cost of something, mostly deemed expensive.",
        "9-9": "Melodramatic to a fault — all is a glorious triumph or mournful tragedy.",
        "10-10": "Absolutely mercenary, will not cooperate without payment, monetary or otherwise."
      }
    },
    "Imperial Navy Personae - Attitude": {
      "name": "Imperial Navy Personae - Attitude",
      "description": "<p>Attitude</p>",
      "results": {
        "1-1": "Dutiful and diligent, but very curious and nosy.",
        "2-2": "Uptight, stuffy, and by-the-book.",
        "3-3": "Cynical and gruff, prefers to help those who don’t go by the book.",
        "4-4": "Resentful of superiors and talks behind their backs — loyal to everyone else.",
        "5-5": "Generally lazy and unreliable for time-sensitive tasks.",
        "6-6": "Miserable, spiteful, goes out of their way to be unhelpful.",
        "7-7": "A schemer, looking for any way to climb their vessel’s political ladder.",
        "8-8": "A genuinely cheerful personality, untouched by the horror of war.",
        "9-9": "Melancholy and subdued, avoids topics or errands where loss of life is likely.",
        "10-10": "Insufferably confident in their particular skills, rarely acknowledges the talents of others."
      }
    },
