    "Hive Spire Encounters": {
      "name": "Hive Spire Encounters",
      "description": "<p>Scenery and Events</p><p></p>",
      "results": {
        "1-7": "You notice the colossal buttresses nearby conglomerate with some of the holdings of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#taj]{House Taj} in a tangled mess of gothic architecture that terminates in a private landing pad. An Aquila Lander pierces the rancid smog clouds and lands. The disembarking delegation from the @UUID[JournalEntry.WE1MLa1KVRHMD8wJ.JournalEntryPage.P8rukYyQeyPJ1ubs]{Imperial Navy} make the sign of the Aquila to the attendant Highborn of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#taj]{House Taj}.",
        "8-14": "A procession honouring the @UUID[Compendium.impmal-core.journals.JournalEntry.B7MZBBT3bNew9N96.JournalEntryPage.X5EFP7IgIUx6CaBW#the-macharian-conquests]{Macharian Crusade} fills the broad street between some of the holdings of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#halvor-mott]{House Halvor-Mott} and a cathedrum. A relic of Saint Macharius — a single, stained glove apparently worn once by the Lord Solar — is held aloft by an @UUID[JournalEntry.pVOsgxlhuYl8D1IJ.JournalEntryPage.ZRtK93OqwboVMET3#adeptus-ministorum]{Adeptus Ministorum} preacher.",
        "15-21": "A gargantuan plasma conduit fills half of the broad @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.lydNVBL1CeXU15kz]{Spire} path before you, sparking slightly as two Tech-Priests work in perfect synchronisation to perform a strange ritual.",
        "22-28": "A @UUID[Compendium.impmal-starter-set.actors.Actor.O49jTi2TzoFQH5GT]{Macharian Vigilite} drags what appears to be a screaming Highborn through an open street, surrounded on all sides by the faded grandeur of the habs of minor nobles. This scenario offers plenty of options for duplicity and adventure — what if the characters rescue this Highborn? Are they truly Highborn, or merely an impostor? Conversely, what if the @UUID[Compendium.impmal-starter-set.actors.Actor.O49jTi2TzoFQH5GT]{Macharian Vigilite} is a fraud? Perhaps they are a ganger attempting to abduct and ransom a noble scion?",
        "29-35": "You pass beneath the grim gaze of a gargantuan statue of a skull-faced Rokarthian warrior, clearly ancient and weathered despite signs of consistent attempts at repairs. A small crowd forms around the statue as several pious young Highborn from the major noble houses attempt the 'Spire Summit', an untethered climb to repair the statue that is considered a mark of honour. If the characters do not intervene, only three scions die — far fewer than the year prior.",
        "36-42": "You emerge from a corridor of towering spires into the open courtyard of a colossal cathedrum. Representatives of noble houses sit beneath acid-resistant parasols as a group of @UUID[JournalEntry.pVOsgxlhuYl8D1IJ.JournalEntryPage.ZRtK93OqwboVMET3#adeptus-ministorum]{Adeptus Ministorum} preachers lead a penitent ceremony. Their attendants are sent to accept castigation by the priests in their stead.",
        "43-49": "As you navigate a complex tangle of buttress-bridges, you come across a palanquin borne by a pair of struggling servitors that seem intent on carrying their charge to the holdings of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#parnam]{House Parnam}. If inspected, the palanquin has a single occupant — a rotting carcass in noble attire who seems to have been dead for days.",
        "50-56": "As you traverse a grand rockrete staircase around a spire, a group of apparently intoxicated nobles practically fall into you, appearing out of the smog. They shout that they will pay a fortune to anyone willing to guide them into the lowest depths of the hive, but initially they will not state why.",
        "57-63": "You emerge from a maze of vertical pathways into a minor courtyard. A nervous crowd surrounds two elderly scions of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#kalveo]{Houses Kalveo} and @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#vylathi]{Vylathi} as they square off and hurl insults at one another, preparing to duel.  As Gamemaster, you might decide the Highborn scions are from different noble houses, whatever best suits your game. They might even ask the characters to fight on their behalf, earning them Influence with one noble house and the ire of the other. You can use the @UUID[Compendium.impmal-starter-set.actors.Actor.bB0rMr6Gez3M9bME]{Ganger} stat-block of [i]The Blazing Seraph[/i] adventure book to represent the Highborn duelists if needed.",
        "64-70": "As the characters make their way through a seemingly abandoned habway connected to one of the Spire’s titanic buttresses, they must all make a [b]Routine (+20) Reflexes (Dodge)[/b] Test or suffer 1 Wound — labour-serfs sworn to @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#castyx]{House Castyx} are in the process of demolishing this area to make way for a 1,000-foot tall statue of Saint Macharius. Shortly afterwards, you encounter a Tech-Priest and an @UUID[JournalEntry.pVOsgxlhuYl8D1IJ.JournalEntryPage.ZRtK93OqwboVMET3#adeptus-ministorum]{Adeptus Ministorum} Preacher arguing with a scion of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#castyx]{House Castyx} about the project.",
        "71-77": "As you navigate through a labyrinthine conurbation of gothic Spire-habs, you encounter an individual who stares at you with absent eyes. You notice they are wearing the robes of the @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#adeptus-astra-telepathica]{Adeptus Astra Telepathica} — an Astropath — and turn away from you to speak to a minor scion of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#kalveo]{House Kalveo}.",
        "78-84": "You exit a twisting system of pathways suspended from buttresses to find yourselves in a partially open-air cathedrum of breathtaking size. You hear the crack of @UUID[Compendium.impmal-starter-set.items.Item.8tlu4X5Qpzl98Uye]{Lasgun} fire as a ceremony of remembrance is held by the @UUID[JournalEntry.pVOsgxlhuYl8D1IJ.JournalEntryPage.ZRtK93OqwboVMET3#adeptus-ministorum]{Adeptus Ministorum}. Representatives of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#taj]{Houses Taj} and @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#halvor-mott]{Halvor-Mott} are in attendance. During the ceremony, preachers add a drop of gathered rainwater to a 100-foot-wide fountain, representing the loss of a single life. This fountain is full to the brim, almost overflowing.",
        "85-91": "Your group exits a sequence of tunnels constructed by the overhanging gothic architecture of Highborn sanctums to come upon an open market with overwhelmingly well-armed security intermingling with the wealthy patrons. You notice a team of @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.Dml6BI69jLrNOQU0#adeptus-administratum]{Adeptus Administratum} inspectors examining every market stall and attendee to ensure they have the proper papers.",
        "92-98": "As you make your way across a buttress-bridge between two Spire towers, several squads of strangely dressed voidsmen push you aside. You see a woman wearing ostentatious wargear stride quickly through the path cleared by her entourage, hurrying alongside a servitor bearing a chained metal box.",
        "99-100": "Your group are lost in the smog, turned around in a labyrinth of faded grandeur and skyscraping spires. You blunder into a walled garden filled with corkscrewing acid-resistant mushrooms in an oil-spill rainbow of colours. Amongst these fungi is Lepis of the @UUID[JournalEntry.Vjfxkwi1rFYPnSIf.JournalEntryPage.O9ywpWJIBMjj5GsS#the-upper-hand]{Upper Hand}, who offers the characters a few diaphanous pieces of extremely sour fungi and an invite to gamble at his establishment in the Steeple District."
      }
    }
  }
}